    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) represents the peak of the 996's mechanical evolution. Powered by a rear-mounted 3.6L M96 flat-six, this naturally aspirated powerplant provides a broad torque curve and exceptional throttle response, paired with a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis benefits from Porsche's refined multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts, delivering high-speed stability and communicative turn-in. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed, including the installation of a dual-row IMS bearing kit and a fresh rear main seal (RMS), mitigating common failure points. The braking system remains sharp with four-piston monobloc aluminum calipers and vented rotors. While the exterior shows the light patina of a well-loved driver, the mechanical synchronization and engine compression remain within tight tolerances, offering a pure, analog driving experience for the discerning purist.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 44
    },
